transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Hi, thank you for calling Viagra at Score Blue. How can I help you today?

Speaker 2: Yes, I'm trying to figure out why you guys sent a second order to my house when I took a first order as a trial error.

Speaker 1: Okay, so let me pull up your account and see how the doctor wrote your prescription.

Speaker 2: Can I get your full name and date of birth?

Speaker 1: First name is David, last name is Williams. Date of birth, April 1st, 1955.

Speaker 2: All right, so I see here the prescription was for the 100 mg Viagra AGV?

Speaker 1: Right.

Speaker 2: Okay. All right, it looks like the doctor wrote it with refills, so that's why it went through the following month,

Speaker 1: but it is not a subscription. You're not required to do it this way.

Speaker 2: If you wanted, you could just pause it, and you could call in and place future orders as needed.

Speaker 1: I don't want future orders. I want to go there. I just want to do it for the first time.

Speaker 2: That's why I made it clear that it was a trial error. I don't want them charging my account and charging somebody more.

Speaker 1: Okay, well, this is an FDA-approved medication that's written by a doctor, so it's a prescription with refills.

Speaker 2: So we can't ever do trials. There are optional refills for you.

Speaker 1: If you want to close out the prescription altogether, I can help you with that.

Speaker 2: Yes.

Speaker 1: Okay, that's very easy.

Speaker 2: Are they charging my account for the second prescription?

Speaker 1: Well, yes, sir, it was charged.

Speaker 2: Well, see, I didn't want that. That's why I made it clear when I first did it. It's going to be a one-time trial for me.

Speaker 1: That's what I was told.

Speaker 2: Normally, if you do it over the phone and say it's a one-time trial, they put a pause on it, but I don't have any notes here for that.

Speaker 1: That being said, if you want to return it, sir, you can.

Speaker 2: You can just put return to sender on that package, okay?

Speaker 1: And you put it right on the label there and put it right back in the mailbox.

Speaker 2: Once that's returned and filed, you'll be issued a refund.

Speaker 1: Okay, well, I want to stop, please. This continues.

Speaker 2: Sure, of course. So upon cancellation, this prescription is officially closed out.

Speaker 1: Any future prescriptions will be limited and with doctor permission and approval.

Speaker 2: Do you accept these terms? So when this is closed out, you won't be able to order this ever again.

Speaker 1: Okay, no problem. Thank you.

Speaker 2: Thank you.

Speaker 1: I want to be able to close it out.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: Because I was just ready to do it as a trial.

Speaker 2: Sure. Okay, you're all set, Mr. Williams.

Speaker 1: Okay. And who am I speaking with so I know when I'm going to contact you?

Speaker 2: This is Nick.

Speaker 1: Nick, okay. So it will be stopped as of today, right?

Speaker 2: As of today, it is closed out.

Speaker 1: And what did they charge me for this second order?

Speaker 2: $63.95, the same amount as the last time, so with your special.

Speaker 1: Okay, I just want to stop, okay?

Speaker 2: Sure, yeah. This prescription is closed out. You won't have access to these refills anymore. It's closed out.

Speaker 1: Okay, thank you so much.

Speaker 2: Thank you.

Speaker 1: Thank you.
